      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the discharge is minimal and you're not experiencing severe pain or fever, you can continue to clean the area with Neosporin and keep it covered with a sterile bandage. Monitor the area closely, and if you notice any worsening symptoms, such as increased redness, swelling, or pain, seek medical attention. However, it's always best to err on the side of caution with post-surgical wounds. Keeping work and appointments in mind, you can probably manage this at home for a day or two, but don't hesitate to consult a healthcare provider if things don't improve.",
      "source": "target",
