      "content": "Apply Neosporin to the wound once a day, preferably at night before bed. This will help keep the area clean and reduce the risk of infection. If you notice any signs of worsening infection, such as increased redness, swelling, warmth, or pus, you should seek medical attention immediately. Remember, it's better to be cautious and proactive about wound care. Keep an eye on it, and don't hesitate to reach out to a healthcare professional if you're concerned.",
